:''See also'' '''[[pavo]]'''

==English==
===Etymology===
Named by Dutch explorers Pieter Dirkszoon Keyser and Frederick de Houtman between 1595 and 1597. From {{L.}} ''[[pavo]]'', a "[[peacock]]"

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia|Pavo (constellation)}}
'''Pavo'''

#{{constellation}}: A [[constellation]] of the [[southern]] sky, said to resemble a [[peacock]]. It lies between the constellations [[Telescopium]] and [[Octans]].

